article.description: Arnaldo Toro had a career-high 22 points plus 18 rebounds as George Washington topped Howard 76-62 on Saturday.
article.headline: Toro scores 22 to lift George Washington past Howard 76-62
article.linkText: Toro scores 22 to lift George Washington past Howard 76-62
article.story: WASHINGTON -- Arnaldo Toro had a career-high 22 points plus 18 rebounds as George Washington topped Howard 76-62 on Saturday. Toro made 9 of 12 shots and the Colonials outshot the Bison from the field 42.6% to 39%. Jamison Battle had 14 points for George Washington (1-1). Mezie Offurum and Justin Williams added 11 apiece. Charles Williams had 21 points for the Bison (0-2). Kyle Foster added 12 points. Khalil Robinson had six rebounds. George Washington plays American at home on Tuesday. Howard plays Notre Dame on the road on Tuesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
